Detailed Description

Implements a thin Session wrapper for the Cipl class.

Author:
Cidana, Inc.
Version:
2.0

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

com.cidana.cipl.CiplSession.CiplSession ( String  session,
Cipl  cipl,
char  escape 
)

Establishes a Session wrapper for the manager.

Multiple session wrappers may be used for a single manager, each one handling a playback instance.

Parameters:
sessionis the session name
ciplis the Playback Manager Cipl instance
escapeis the escape character used when opening Manager.

String [] com.cidana.cipl.CiplSession.execute ( String  command)

Executes a command in for the session.

This is the principal method of controlling playback.

Parameters:
commandis the command to execute, e.g. "play".
Returns:
String array of three strings
returnArray[0] Error condition (if not empty). This will be one of the accepted CiplError names.
returnArray[1] If successful return data is a string blob here. May be empty or "".
returnArray[2] unused. returns exactly ""

CSplitBlob com.cidana.cipl.CiplSession.show ( String  property)

Shows the given (complex) state or property.

Equivalent to
show
"device" [(Number)]
"service" [(Number)]
"program" [(Number)]
"programpresent" [(Number)]
"programfollow" [(Number)]
"programschedule" [(Number)]
"audio" [(Number)]
"subtitle" [(Number)]

Parameters:
propertyis the property name
Returns:
A string blob or null on error.
Return values:
StringShow device returns an 2D array of all devices, or for a particular Index_Number. Each row represents a device is as follows:
(device_UID) (device_ID) (device_NAME) (device_TYPE) (device_STANDARD) (sourcetype)
To select a device, either the position in the 2D array or the device_UID can be used. It is generally preferrable to use the device_UID as that will not change if a device is added or subtracted dynamically.

Show service returns a 2D array of all services or for a particular Index_Number. Each row represents a service as follows:
(service_UID) (service_NAME) (service_PROVIDERNAME) (service_LOCATION) (service_URL) (service_TYPE) (service_CA) (service_LCN)
To select a service, either the position in the 2D array or the service_UID can be used. It is generally preferrable to use the service_UID as that will not change if a service is added or subtracted dynamically.

Show program/programpresent/programfollow/programschedule returns a 2D array of programs associated with the designated Service_Number(current service is used if unspecified).
(program_NAME) (program_DESCRIPTION) (program_STARTDATE) (program_ENDDATE) (program_ENCRYPTED)
To select a program, the position in the 2D array can be used.

Show audio returns a 2D array of audio languages associated with the designated Service_Number (current service is used if unspecified).
(Language_CODE)
The index in the 2D array is used for selection. The Language_CODE is a 3 character code, and may be "N/A" if not specified.

Show country returns a 2D array of country information. Each row represents a country is as follows:
(country_NAME) (country_CODE)

Show region returns a 2D array of region information associated with the designated Counrty_Code. Each row represents a region is as follows:
(region_NAME) (region_ID) [frequency_BEGIN~frequency_END] ...

CiplError com.cidana.cipl.CiplSession.startReScanFrequency ( int  startKhz,
int  endKhz,
int  bandwidthKhz 
)

Starts a re-scan of a tuner.

Scans are asynchronous, so you should wait for the scan event or issue a "wait scan". Equivalent to
startrescan startKhz endKhz bandwidthKhz

Parameters:
startKhzis the starting khz (or channel for ATSC)
endKhzis the ending khz (or channel for ATSC)
bandwidthKhzis the bandwidth of each channel.
Returns:
CI_SOK on success.
CI_EFAIL on failure.
CI_EUNEXPECTED if manager not open or not available. CI_EACCESSDENIED missing set sys cache path, you should set it before scan.
